args: Zzz... Hnrf? Emilia? Where are you?!
Don't worry, sweetie. Your big sis isn't\ngoing anywhere; I'll always be right here\nat your side, okay?
Thanks, Emilia... I'm not lonely anymore...
(On the surface, she seems better,\nbut you can tell her heart's still hurting.)
(I need to work harder to make sure\nshe never feels lonely again!)
Anna, are you all right?! Can you stand?!
*sniffle* It hurts and I can't walk.
One express horsey ride home, coming up!
Blech! Carrots and peppers are GROSS.
You can have mine, Emilia!\nEat them all up for me, 'kay?
What? You shouldn't be picky, Anna...
...Oh, all right. But just this once!
Yaaay! I love you soooo much!
And so the days passed with Melsa\never at Anna's side. Until finally...
(She slept through the night without\nwaking up in tears this entire week.)
(It seems like her scars really are\nbeginning to heal.)
(My role here is coming to an end...)
(Which means it's time to end this and let\nboth of us go back to our real lives.)
Yah! Hrah! ...Gah?! I lost my grip!
Whoa! You messed up the spinny move?!
I did, huh. Isn't that funny?
(Now that she's had time to heal, she may\nbe ready to accept her sister's death.)
(But if I just throw the truth in her face,\nthe shock could do terrible damage.)
(If possible, I'd like to lead her to\nlearning the truth on her own.)
Pretty weird, huh, Anna? It turns out I may\nnot be that good with a spear after all.
Are you not feeling good?!\nDid you catch a bad cold again?!
Er, no. I... That isn't what I—
(Perhaps that was a bit too subtle.)
(I'll have to make my next hint\na touch easier to follow.)
Here, Emilia! If you've got a fever,\nyou gotta put ice on your forehead!
Thank you—oh, but not the forehead.\nA little higher up, please.
That's right. Would you set the ice\nright on the top of my head?
Okay! ...Huh? It won't stay.\nYour big dumb ears are in the...
That's right—I have great big ears coming\nout of the top of my head! You don't have\nbig ears like mine, do you, Anna?
Isn't that funny? We're sisters,\nso why would we be different?
SOOOO CUTE! You look like a bunny!\nI wish I had big ears like you!
I want to grow my own pair of bunny ears!\nShow me how! Show me, show meeeee!
And so Melsa's attempts to guide Anna\nto the truth continued apace.
I guess that just leaves the final option:\nTelling her the truth in plain language.
It feels so cruel to hurt her like that\nwhen she's just starting to feel better.
Oh, but this is simply awful.\nWhat am I going to do?
